@node History "ImGauge Documentation - History"

Note - Version 1.3 has been unreleased for 2 years since I got no registrations.

@{b}V 1.3 - (27 JUN 1996)@{ub}

        Enhancement - now displaying & processing the percentage value on
                      float-level
        Enhancement - displaying the elapsed rendering time and (!) the
                      estimated time for the scene
        Enhancement - now checks Imagine's state every second. This looks
                      better in conjunction with the elapsed time

@{b}V 1.2 - (22 FEB 1996)@{ub}

        Now using SCALAR ® Routines V1.0
        BUGFIX! Fixed one harmless enforcer hit (byte read).

@{b}V 1.1 - (31 JAN 1996)@{ub}

        Minor optical enhancement in the GUI routines

@{b}V 1.0 - (4 JAN 1996)@{ub}

        Initial release
@endnode

@node PGP "ImGauge Documentation - PGP Signatures"

To ensure that you get an unmodified version of ImGauge,  I've  included  PGP
signatures   for  every  important  file  (all  files  ending  with  '.asc'  or
'.sig' are signatures). The PGP signatures have been created using PGP 5.0 Amiga.
Since I'm using  a  @{i}Diffie-Hellman@{ui}  key you will only be able to verify the PGP signatures
with PGP 5.0 or above.

My public key can be found @{" here " link PUBKEY},  but  it's  not  needed  for
verifying signatures.

You can verify the files with the following command:

pgpv @{i}filename.asc@{ui}

where @{i}filename.asc@{ui} is the name of the signature file.



You can download the latest AMIGA PGP5 version at:

        http://www.amitar.com.au/~stef/

@endnode

